<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01033i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01033i">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01033i"> 33(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Shop T p (trade price line) ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[GRADING THE SHOPPER. By A FIRST SALESWOMAN.]</font> Every person entering a large drapery store is mentally &ldquo;graded&rdquo; by the shopgirl serving her according to the manner in which she makes her purchases. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> It is the type of <i>shopper</i> we study, and we classify these types under headings which are universally used by shop assistants throughout the country. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Different goods are known as &ldquo;lines&rdquo; by shoppers. <mark>Shoppers in turn are known as &ldquo;lines&rdquo;</mark> by the assistants. <small> <a name="DM17nov22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DM17nov22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (17 November 1922) 8/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05111g" href="c05all.htm#c05111g">VI.C.05:111(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
